Clairement pas. The creature merely whistled and tried to charge straight at Thassalin. Fortunately, despite its size, he was agile enough to dodge, but Nyssi couldn't help but scream when she nearly lost her grip on her too slippery scales.
"HOW DO YOU KILL THEM ?", cried Nyssi.
"GO FOR THEIR HEADS !"
"IT'S NOT GOING TO BE EASY !"
Thassalin blew out a breath, then circled around to approach the mountain he called home. The black beast followed, becoming somewhat frantic when it was struck by a bolt of fire from behind. The creature hadn't noticed it wasn't alone anymore. Its panic grew as Thassalin slowed down, then struck the beast's head with his tail, causing it to veer off course.
Groaning and whistling, the creature took altitude and spat into the air. Suddenly, everything turned black, as if the monster was sucking the light from the sky and replacing it with a perpetual cloud of night.
With no visibility, Thassalin tried to retreat, but he grazed the treetops before crashing into the clearing. As if it knew exactly where he had fallen, the creature charged straight for him, dragging the dark cloud in its wake.
"Kayel!," exclaimed Tenuk as he emerged from the cloud and began circling to try and spot Nyssi and Thassalin below, in the darkness. "What do we do, Kayel? Kayel...? Kayel, where are you?"
Below, Nyssi managed to rise to her feet. She was sure she had broken something, but her unusual healing powers, far from natural, had already started to take effect. That could not be said for Thassalin, who lay sprawled on a mound, propped against the only tree that had not bent under his weight. Nyssi did her best to try and reach Thassalin, but she could not see two meters in front of her. Everything was plunged into darkness, engulfed in the unholy shadows. And within those shadows, something roared.
A terrible cudgel-like tail came crashing down next to Nyssi, sending her tumbling back. However, she noted that the tail was thrashing without aiming. From what Nyssi could see and hear of the creature, it growled and scratched the shadows it had conjured. Something teleported through the darkness, striking the monster, disorienting it.
A gunshot rang out suddenly, and the monster collapsed silently, inert. The darkness surrounding them dissipated, revealing what had happened. Standing atop the creature was Kayel, gun in hand and breathing hard.
"It's... the strangest shadow jump I've ever made... Thanto kat'olon...", panted Kayel. His eyes glowed with a black light, and a dark energy coursed through his body. However, as he spoke, Kayel's organic plating returned to its color, and his eyes resumed their normal yellow hue.
It took Nyssi a moment to understand what had occurred. They all knew that Kayel possessed strange shadow powers. He rarely used them, as most people considered them blasphemous and rather terrifying. But Nyssi didn't know that Kayel could use these powers in the dark. And, judging by his behavior, Kayel seemed just as surprised as they were.
"Are you okay ?", Nyssi couldn't help but ask.
"Yes, I'm fine. I killed something. It'll be better in a minute." Kayel examined his work as Tenuk made his way to land beside him, reverting to his normal Spast form.
Now that the creature was still, they could see better what it was. Its skin was black as coal and sticky, but the slime continued to adhere to its body. It had four wings and four limbs, each ending in long claws, and two straight horns protruded from its skull.
Before Tenuk and Kayel could ask what that thing was, something howled and lunged from a nearby bush. However, the beast didn't have time to reach them, as a familiar vehicle crash-landed on its flank, sending it tumbling to Nyssi's feet. Not taking any chances, she grabbed her rifle and immediately shot it in the head, killing the creature on the spot.
"Oops...", muttered Retvik from the driver's seat, before clumsily shutting off the engine and jumping out of the truck. "I, uh, didn't mean to do that. Are you all right?"
"You missed all the action", regretted Tenuk. "Where were you?"
"You all dropped me. I came here as fast as I could", sighed Retvik. "Can anyone tell me what those disgusting things are?"
The question from Retvik received a response from Thassalin, who had just stood up. He was cut and scratched everywhere and seemed a bit disoriented, but he didn't look too badly injured.
"YOU KILLED THE CORRUPTIDS! THE INFECTED MONSTERS. CREATURES LEFT HERE WHEN THE CORRUPTION ATTACKED YOUR GODS."
"You mean... the horrible god-monster that we... helped kill?", stammered Tenuk.
"YES. EXACTLY. THERE MIGHT BE MORE OF THEM, BUT I DIDN'T SUCCEED IN Hitting THEIR HEADS. I'M SHORT OF A GUN. AND TWO AGAINST ONE, THAT'S NOT FAIR, IS IT?" Thassalin approached Kayel and patted his head. "THANK YOU, LITTLE ONE. YOU REMIND ME OF MY OLD FRIEND ARKADIN. BUT LESS KILLER AND LESS ABLE TO KILL UNIVERSES."
"Uh... thank you... I suppose", said Kayel shrugging. "So, we're done here, right?"
Nyssi shrugged, then grabbed her camera to photograph the beasts now definitively dead. She then took out her favorite dagger, the Death God's dagger, and began cutting one of the creature's horns, before moving on to the other. But as she finished, the creatures flamed up and quickly turned into heaps of ashes. The same thing happened to the horns that Nyssi had cut.
"Well... it's both convenient and not at all convenient", she sighed. "At least, I still have the photos..."
